 about Logi Analytics, was mentioned as unsubstantiated, which might lead to confusion. May require further cross-checking to ensure reliability. ### Comparison and Accuracy Check: - **Consistency**: All models mention platforms such as Looker Studio, AgencyAnalytics, and Google Search Console, showing consistency in available tools for generating report links. - **Gaps and Overlaps**: Each model captures unique details about various platforms but overlaps in describing Looker Studio and AgencyAnalytics processes significantly. - **Cross-Check**: The provided references confirm the accuracy regarding how different platforms handle report linking processes, like the role of `Get report link` in Looker Studio and specifics around report linking in MicroStrategy. ### Key Insights: - Most platforms have a straightforward process involving a 'share' or 'export' function to generate report links. - Customization options for shared reports are common, such as setting date ranges or user permissions. - Each platform has unique steps and limitations, emphasizing the importance of understanding individual system features and documented steps for accurate linking. Finding a Link to Your Report Generating a Shareable Report Link Most platforms provide a method to create a shareable link for your reports. Here's how you can generate these links across different tools: Google Looker Studio: In the upper-right corner, click the down arrow next to 'Share' and select 'Get report link'. Ensure you have shared the report with recipients, granting them at least 'Viewer' access. Use 'Link to your current report view' if you want the recipient to see the report with current filters and settings1. AgencyAnalytics: Access 'Reports' from the left-side menu, search for your report, and select the 'Share' option. Configure the date range and other settings before clicking 'Create Link'. You can review previously generated links by navigating to 'Activity' > 'Links'4. MicroStrategy: Open the report by either clicking the report name in a linked document or through Presentation/Editable Mode. Use right-click menus to navigate through links embedded in documents or reports5. ReportsNow: Utilize the 'Report Link' tool to create a URL or command-line entry to directly access and execute a report, dashboard, or ProReport8. Accessing Existing Reports or Links Sometimes accessing a report link involves using navigation within a tool: Google Search Console: The 'Links' report allows you to view backlinks to your site, including 'Top linked pages', 'Top linking sites', and more. It provides options to export data as CSV or Google Sheets3. IBM Systems: Linking within IBM includes selecting a column or chart and configuring navigation properties. This includes filtering based on selected data or applying existing report filters2. Linking Between Reports Many systems enable internal linking between reports: Logi Analytics: In the Insert Link dialog, select 'Report' to connect another report6. Syniti: Access the Page Columns Vertical View to configure controls that link to specific reports10. Enhanced Sharing Features Looker Studio: Upon generating a report link, ensure proper sharing settings via 'View sharing settings', which includes the permission level for users. For public sharing, note that uninvited viewers will not see ownership details1. AgencyAnalytics: Customize your link sharing with options like setting comparison periods and allowing date changes. Links are read-only, and dynamic reports have unique icons indicating their status4. Using these methods, you can easily find or generate a link to your report, tailored to your platform and specific needs. How to customize sharing settings in Looker Studio? What are the export limitations in Google Search Console's Links report? How to enable navigation links in IBM systems? Mixture-of-Agents Search Web"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/age